    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>at an angle</p><p>Add the<strong> sliced carrot</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>meat-free sausages</strong> to the tray and put everything in the oven for 20 min or until the meat-free sausages are cooked through</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the carrot and meat-free<strong> </strong>sausages are cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a very low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8 min or until softened and caramelised</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Tip: If you'd rather skin-off mash, peel the potatoes first</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, add your <strong>onion marmalade </strong>and <strong>Henderson's Relish </strong>and mix until fully combined \u2013 this is your <strong>onion gravy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has caramelised, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min, stirring until they're evenly coated in the flour</p><p>Add the <strong>onion gravy stock</strong>, increase the heat to medium and cook for 7-8 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>red onion gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the gravy thickens, trim your <strong>green beans</strong>, then add them to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p><p>Tip: For a speedy alternative, add your green beans to a small bowl with a splash of cold water and microwave, covered, for 1-2 min</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the green beans are boiling, return the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/extra-special-meat-free-bangers-n-sweet-potato-mash/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> meat-free sausages</strong> over the <strong>mash</strong> with the <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>green beans </strong>to the side</p><p>Pour the <strong>red onion gravy </strong>all over and enjoy!</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Loved this recipe? Keep an eye out for it on the Everyday Favourites section of our menu.</span></strong></p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
